refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayarray_fill intstart_index intcount mixedvalue
Fills an array with count entries of the value of the value parameter, keys starting at the start_index parameter.

&reftitle.errors;


 Throws a ValueError if count is
 out of range.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     array_fill now throws a ValueError
     if count is out of range; previously E_WARNING
     was raised, and the function returned &false;.

&reftitle.examples;
array_fill example
<?php $a = array_fill(5, 6, 'banana'); print_r($a); ?>
&example.outputs;
Array ( [5] => banana [6] => banana [7] => banana [8] => banana [9] => banana [10] => banana )
array_fill example with a negative start index
<?php $a = array_fill(-2, 4, 'pear'); print_r($a); ?>
&example.outputs.7;
Array ( [-2] => pear [0] => pear [1] => pear [2] => pear )
&example.outputs.8;
Array ( [-2] => pear [-1] => pear [0] => pear [1] => pear )
Note that index '-1' is not present prior to PHP 8.0.0.

&reftitle.notes;


 See also the Arrays 
 section of manual for a detailed explanation of negative keys.
